<Layout title={`${blogPost.title} - Day 41 Thrive`}>
    <Header />
    <main class="blog-post">
        <article class="container">
            <header class="post-header">
                <h1>{blogPost.title}</h1>
                <div class="post-meta">
                    <span class="date">{blogPost.date}</span>
                    <span class="author">By {blogPost.author}</span>
                </div>
                <p class="subtitle">(How to Build a Team That Solves Problems Instead of Bringing Them to You)</p>
            </header>
            <div class="post-content">
                <h2>Introduction: Are You the Brainâ€¦ or the Bottleneck?</h2>
                <p>Every leader hits this moment: You've built the systems, written the checklists, handed over the SOPsâ€¦ And yet your team still asks, "What should I do next?"</p>
                
                <p>At first, it feels good to be needed. Eventually, it just feels heavy.</p>
                
                <p>At Day 41 Thrive, we believe the goal of leadership isn't to create followers. It's to create decision-makersâ€”people who think, act, and care like owners.</p>
                
                <p>You don't need a team that completes tasks. You need a team that takes ownership.</p>
                
                <p>Let's talk about how to make that shift.</p>

                <h2>Phase 1: From "Do This" to "Think Through This"</h2>
                <p>Most businesses start with task-based training. It's necessaryâ€”but it's not enough.</p>
                
